<subSubSection id="6CBF1937BDDBE5E0CD053FBD8C4D66F5" pageNumber="869" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="90053ABF1DD5D6E1A04DD3B083370B61" pageNumber="869">
<emphasis id="AF9055299ECE3BF227E42AAD53621EDD" italics="true" pageNumber="869">Note:</emphasis>
Grierson (in 
<emphasis id="E635F2014A5B751CFE8D90178CF2D22B" italics="true" pageNumber="869">Ceylon J. Sci., Biol. Sci.</emphasis>
11: 17-18. 1974), in a detailed study, rejected 
<specimenReference id="2E9EE3E4634B253D04A48D7FE6FA800E" collectionCode="BM" specimenCode="15">
Herb. Hermann 2: 15, No. 312 (
<collectionCode id="7D650B95D4219CD1E0C3E8B282E61A8C">BM</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as a possible 
<typeStatus id="6F82126BF3147B1B4D1F74B89BF08506">lectotype</typeStatus>
as it conflicts with 
<normalizedToken id="DA17F754C55E45A2DE3B3BD76C1D39B7" originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
diagnosis, and appeared to argue in favour of 1044.1 (LINN) as the type. Unfortunately, the LINN sheet lacks a 
<emphasis id="CFF09C6011FC94619DFD157608F7BDF9" italics="true" pageNumber="869">
<volumeTitle id="948CF8D46E37C5897A35F211CE3ABC94">Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken id="FE8109D172CE01723698EE4D1F6E025C" originalValue="“1”">&quot;1&quot;</normalizedToken>
) and is evidently a post-1753 addition to the herbarium and not original material for the name. Oddly, Grierson later (in Dassanayake &amp; Fosberg, 
<emphasis id="76D710A7819220371408E62A2705563B" italics="true" pageNumber="869">Revised Handb. Fl. Ceylon</emphasis>
1:81. 1980) referred to the Hermann material as type. 
<normalizedToken id="C53647CC4F0C7B7FF3977918F809CA98" originalValue="Anderberg’s">Anderberg's</normalizedToken>
choice therefore has priority.
</paragraph>
